Steps to implement the project:

1. Go to Spring Initialzr, select java, maven, choose version, give the name of project.
2. Select the required dependencies(Spring Web, Spring Data JPA, MySQL Driver, Validation).

3. Setup Instructions:
a) Create Database

Open MySQL and run:

CREATE DATABASE expense_tracker;

b) Create MySQL User

Run:

CREATE USER 'appuser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'AppPass123';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON expense_tracker.* TO 'appuser'@'localhost';

CREATE USER 'Your_Username'@'127.0.0.1' IDENTIFIED BY 'Your_Password';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON expense_tracker.* TO 'Your_Username'@'127.0.0.1';

FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

c) application.properties

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/expense_tracker
spring.datasource.username=Your_Username
spring.datasource.password=Your_Password

spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.MySQLDialect

4. Create the required classes and write the code.
5. Run the main class and open the url on server.
6.Test the API with Postman, by using CRUD opeations and view the result.

Conclusion:
This project is a clean and simple example demonstrating:

1. Spring Boot
2. MySQL
3. Spring Data JPA
4. Hibernate
5. CRUD operations
6. Postman testing



